    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Retention Policy: A retention policy determines at what point an annotation is discarded. It is s specified using Java's built-in annotations: <code>@Retention</code><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/49632147/4770877\"><sup>[About]</sup></a></p>\n\n<pre><code>1.SOURCE: annotation retained only in the source file and is discarded\n          during compilation.\n2.CLASS: annotation stored in the .class file during compilation,\n         not available in the run time.\n3.RUNTIME: annotation stored in the .class file and available in the run time.\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6482784,
      "reputation" : 369,
      "user_id" : 5019291,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/yWqC9.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Michael Wong",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5019291/michael-wong"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1586832250,
    "creation_date" : 1586832250,
    "answer_id" : 61199934,
    "question_id" : 3107970,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<ul>\n<li><strong>CLASS</strong>\n：Annotations are to be recorded in the class file by the compiler but need not be retained by the VM at run time.</li>\n<li><strong>RUNTIME</strong>\n：Annotations are to be recorded in the class file by the compiler and retained by the VM at run time, so they may be read reflectively.</li>\n<li><strong>SOURCE</strong>\n：Annotations are to be discarded by the compiler.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/annotation/RetentionPolicy.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Oracle Doc</a></p>\n"
  } ],
